<sections><clause id="_bd6cd4f9-e5dc-474c-a833-0ab23be58e98" unnumbered="true" obligation="normative">

<p id="_63aa9a70-9e30-4d32-af4b-869221e6f9b2">
<strong><sup>1</sup>H neutral atom, <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi>S</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>S</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></stem> unperturbed optical transition</strong>
</p>
</clause>
<clause id="_recommended_value_of_the_frequency" obligation="normative"><title>Recommended value <eref type="inline" bibitemid="cipm-rec2" citeas="[1]"/> of the frequency</title><p id="_afc4d648-f911-46d4-9d74-8a1168fb678b">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1233030706593514</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</p>
<p id="_c8c4c72c-8829-4626-8e66-358bf99eda28">equivalent to</p>
<p id="_9869f57f-f969-42c8-b711-f45cedfd18ca"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="italic"><mi>&#955;</mi></mstyle><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>243134624.626044</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_fm"><mi mathvariant="normal">fm</mi></mrow>








</math></stem>,</p>
<p id="_aee1302e-1270-49be-83e3-975bffa36304">with an estimated relative standard uncertainty of <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem>.</p>
<note id="_239d78cf-91c1-4a5a-8f39-9dd0f685260e">
<p id="_8e4ab6b4-800f-40f9-8be9-0ae9bb83460c">The <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mstyle mathvariant="normal"><mrow><mn>1</mn><mi>S</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>S</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></stem> transition is excited by two photons of the frequency <stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>1233</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_THz"><mi mathvariant="normal">THz</mi></mrow>








</math></stem></p>
</note></clause>
<clause id="_source_data" obligation="normative"><title>Source data</title><dl id="_60477ff2-5df1-4024-8e97-3a2bae01e2b9">
<dt>Adopted value</dt>
<dd>
<p id="_1a3785ee-437f-4873-9b01-2b6df91d3664"><stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1233030706593514</mn><mo rspace="thickmathspace">&#8290;</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem><br/>
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><msub><mrow><mi>u</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mn>15</mn></mrow></mrow></msup></math></stem></p>
</dd>
</dl>
<p id="_4d7dbd90-75cd-43b1-8a7b-829422b059e8">calculated from</p>
<table id="_3d87305b-0ca2-45b6-9985-b9c42b6a06b5" unnumbered="true">
<thead>
<tr>
<th valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced open="(" close=")"><mrow><msup><mrow><mtext/></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mtext>H</mtext></mrow></mfenced><mo>/</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</th>
<th valign="top" align="center">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mi>u</mi><mo>/</mo><mrow xref="U_NISTu31"><mi mathvariant="normal">Hz</mi></mrow>









</math></stem>
</th>
<th valign="top" align="center">source data</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>2466061413187035</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="center">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>10</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="center">
<eref type="inline" bibitemid="parthey" citeas="[2]"/>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top" align="left">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>2466061413187018</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="center">
<stem type="MathML"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mn>11</mn></math></stem>
</td>
<td valign="top" align="center">
<eref type="inline" bibitemid="matveev" citeas="[3]"/>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p id="_48588189-fca2-4ce7-a427-ec0f3c758527">as a weighted mean of the above values divided by two.</p>
<p id="_bfae5634-42e7-4fb5-b75a-0504272c2844">Given the noticeable drift of the values of the past measurements
<eref type="inline" bibitemid="matveev" citeas="[3]"/> and the fact that the values come from a single
laboratory the CCTF considered it prudent to attribute an increased
standard uncertainty by a factor of three.</p></clause>
